The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques, specifically neural networks, to classify facial attractiveness. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the potential biases that can occur in the data selection and network architectures, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of these automated beauty competitions on the cultural landscape, which falls under the cyberculture (cs.CY) sub-category.
